Rhondda Tunnel was closed as part of the Beeching Report in 1968 . 
  It runs 1,000 feet beneath the Welsh hills . 
  Engineers are due to visit the tunnel next week to see whether it is safe to use as a cycle route . 
  The tunnel was opened in 1890 in the coal boom and was closed in 1968  . 
  It runs from Blaencwm in the Rhondda Valley to Blaengwynfi in the Afan Valley  . 
  The tunnel could be Britain's longest cycle tunnel  . 
 